INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (199,3,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h2 align=\"center\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">SE Master Class Series:<br />Emotions and Memory – A Hidden Dimension of Somatic Experiencing®</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">September 30th to October 4th, 2012&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">Chester, CT</h2> <p>&nbsp;</p> <address style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">(Open to SE Students who have completed Intermediate and above. Contact the <a title=\"Email Info@traumahealing.com\" href=\"mailto:info@traumahealing.com?subject=SE Master Class - Emotions and Memory with Peter Levine\">Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute</a> to enroll. See the Flyer <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/se_masterclass-emotions_memory_Oct_20121.pdf\" title=\"Event Flyer (PDF)\" target=\"_parent\">Here</a>)</span></address> <p>The Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a four day, exclusive graduate-level training with Peter A. Levine, PhD, recognized author and developer of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model. This workshop is a rare opportunity to study with the originator of SE® focusing on two of the most misunderstood, nuanced, aspects of working with trauma within the SE® Model.</p> <p>In working with trauma, SE® Practitioners are often confused about the roles of emotions and memory in the resolution of trauma; mainly, that SE® doesn’t need to deal with them. This is wholly untrue.</p> <p>While emotions can interfere with trauma therapy, the deeper truth is that helping clients access and learn from their natural emotions is fundamental to good therapy and is an essential part of the healing process. Specifically, we will explore how certain emotions, such as disgust and anger are “gatekeepers,” keys to opening up to other emotions and to living a fuller, wiser, more vital life.</p> <p>Traumatic memory is one of the most misunderstood and contentious issues in trauma treatment today. Part of this confusion stems from a limited comprehension surrounding the nature and complexity of memory. There are multiple memory systems in the brain and body ranging from those most conscious (so called “normal” or declarative memories) to implicit (emotional) and procedural (so called body) memories, which are deeply unconscious. Each of these memory systems must be approached in a uniquemanner and then integrated into a coherent narrative.</p> <p>During this training, we will explore how to work with your clients’ emotions and memories more masterfully within the SE® model, weaving these crucial aspects of experience together through the trauma re-negotiation process. We will also learn skills to avoid the generation of “false memories”, and to ensure the maximum resolution and integration of traumatic experience and the restoration of wholeness.</p>','Emotions and Memory – A Hidden Dimension of Somatic Experiencing®','','draft','open','open','','emotions-and-memory-a-hidden-dimension-of-somatic-experiencingr','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',0,'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/?p=199',10,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (200,3,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" title=\"Full Size\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" alt=\"Case_consult\" width=\"612\" height=\"612\" /></a></p> <p>The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and supervision with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>\"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner.\" </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://events.constantcontact.com/register/event?llr=qbahuwcab&amp;oeidk=a07e6rljj4m88755a32\" title=\"Constant Contact Event Page - Enroll Now!\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>You can register here. Space is extremely limited.</strong></span></a></p> <p>Please contact Joan Luly for <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/caseconsultflyer1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">more information</a>: <a href=\"mailto:joansehealing@mac.com\">joansehealing@mac.com</a>.</p> <p>If you are interested in having Peter see a client of yours, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href=\"mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com\">traumahealing@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;with the following information:</p> <ol> <li>First name and age of client.</li> <li>Brief list of relevant trauma history (Including the age that it occurred)</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is stuck.</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is advancing.</li> <li>Why do you specifically want Peter to see this client.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <p>NOTE: NO cancellations can be made after January 16th, 2013. Thank you.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>','Peter Levine Group Case Consultation in San Diego - January 19th!','','draft','open','open','','peter-levine-group-case-consultation-in-san-diego-january-19th','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',0,'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/?p=200',9,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (201,3,'2013-01-17 19:09:17','2013-01-17 19:09:17','<h4>Introduction:</h4> <p>Hi everyone, thanks for enrolling in Peter Levine\'s events. We hope you find this an enriching experience, both professionally and personally. This just lays down some ground rules that we have developed over time to establish certain boundaries.&nbsp;</p> <h4>Cancellation Policy: &nbsp;</h4> <p>We\'ve (as in Peter Levine and his representatives - Justin Snavely, and his coordinators) been having issues with people not taking Peter\'s consults seriously, taking a spot and then canceling at the last minute and expecting a refund. This takes away opportunities for other therapists to learn from Peter. So we have had to say that we will gladly refund you your money if you cancel up to 3 days before the event, as that leaves the coordinator enough time to contact the waiting list and get someone to take your spot. But if you can\'t organize yourself enough to do that, and cancel later than the 3 day cut-off, then we reserve the right to keep your money. If you asked to pay by check or cash, we also reserve the right for you to pay us, like a client would a missed appointment. &nbsp;If you are a jerk, then we WILL add you to a list of people that we will ban from any future Peter Levine event. That sucks, and we don\'t want to do it. But it is a possibility. We know that you are all professionals and this is totally the minority and not the norm. &nbsp;We also know that bad stuff happens and there is nothing to do about it, and we promise to honor those occasional, authentic emergencies where you can\'t make it, due to illness, family problems, death, injuries and accidents, all that stuff, and we won\'t be jerks in return and hold onto your money if you have a valid reason. By confirming your order, you promise that you will honor this.&nbsp;</p> <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3em;\">Confidentiality:</span></p> <p>What happens at the Case Consultation, STAYS AT THE CASE CONSULTATION! Ya Dig? This is people\'s private stuff. We are professionals, dangit!</p> <h4>Putting up with tech equipment and your Video Release:</h4> <p>Peter Levine tapes everything. So there is the chance that your voice and image will be recorded, and can be used for training or marketing materials in a variety of formats, media, or venues. You say you are okay with this. You claim no ownership to the material, and will not hold Peter Levine or his representatives responsible for anything that might effect you in some negative way that could possibly happen in the future. In other words, you won\'t sue us.&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Again, by confirming your order, you agree to these things. Thanks for reading, hope it is clear, if you have any issues or questions, or I missed something, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href=\"mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com?subject=Terms%20and%20Conditions\" target=\"_blank\">traumahealing@gmail.com</a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>','Terms and Conditions','','publish','open','open','','terms-and-conditions','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',0,'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/17/terms-and-conditions/',1,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (202,3,'2013-01-17 08:00:00','2013-01-17 08:00:00','<h2>Instructions:</h2> <p>A Demo session between Peter A Levine PhD and Jana, a woman who was profiled on KTLA for her incredible 5 year battle (c. 2010) with PTSD following a full awakening while under Anesthesia.</p> <p>For your convenience and highest quality, Please use the link to download the video directly to your computer. Right-Click on the two links below and choose \"Save Target As...\" or \"Save Link As...\" (depending on your system). Then tell the computer where and what-name you want it saved as. I would recommend saving to the desktop. Then wait a while for it to download. Once it\'s done, find where you saved your file and then play it. It should be compatible with most media players out there.</p> <p>If this doesn\'t work for you, then please use the streaming version below. It can be played inside the browser. Please be patient while it downloads.&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"direct\"></a>Direct Download (Right click and \"Save Link As...\")</h2> <ul> <li> <h3><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"images/stories/video/jana/jana.mp4\">Jana</a>&nbsp;(1.4GB)</h3> </li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"flash\"></a>\"Streaming\" versions&nbsp;</h2> <p>*please be patient as it downloads.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Jana-</h3> <p>{flowplayer size=768x432 img=http://somaticexperiencing.com/Video/preview/jana_img.png}images/stories/video/jana/jana.mp4{/flowplayer}</p> <p>History: Jana was a friend of the coordinator of the class that Peter was holding to teach practioners of Somatic Experiencing® how to engage with Near Death and Anesthesia States. Jana graciously provided herself as a demonstration. Contains segments from KTLA. With permission. This demonstrates what Peter Levine has been discussing for years as one of the MOST OVERLOOKED sources of trauma (as well as the leading factor that leads to future vulnerability to trauma), \"routine\" surgical procedures. It doesn\'t just have to be full awakening, but also a partial or \"threshold\" awakening where there is no memory, but the body remembering being cut into. This is why Dr. Levine is an ardent champion of the immediate adoption of anesthesiologists utilizing EKG scanners, as well as providing local anesthetic, as well as a general pain reliever on par with morphine.:</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>','Somatic Experiencing©: Jana - Full Awakening Under Anesthesia','','publish','open','open','','somatic-experiencingc-jana-full-awakening-under-anesthesia','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',0,'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/17/somatic-experiencingc-jana-full-awakening-under-anesthesia/',5,'post','',0);
