INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (344,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<p><a href=\"http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php\" title=\"Go to Register Now\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.womenssymposium.org/images/2013-save-the-date.jpg\" alt=\"Womens Symposium Save the Date\" width=\"300\" height=\"170\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" /></a></p> <p>Dr. Levine will be participating as a speaker at the 2013 Women’s Symposium. The Women’s Symposium is a one-day event featuring women leaders in the field of addiction, behavioral health, and women’s issues. Our 2013 Women’s Symposium message is a “Journey to Wholeness.”<span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">&nbsp;This year’s topics are practical, solution-focused and designed to enrich the skills of professionals within the field of addiction treatment and those who treat addicted women.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Check out their site for <a href=\"http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php\" title=\"Women\'s Symposium Homepage\" target=\"_blank\">more info.</a></p>','Speaking at the Betty Ford Center\'s Women\'s Symposium  on March 21st at UCLA','','inherit','open','open','','213-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',213,'http://localhost:8888/speed/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (345,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<p>One of Peter\'s classic videos - Jody, My Ears, My Tears and My Fears, is one of the seminal training videos in the Somatic Experiencing®.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Jody-</h3> <p>&nbsp;</p> <br /> <iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/58570494\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>','Jody - My Ears, My Tears, My Fears','','inherit','open','open','','212-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',212,'http://localhost:8888/speed/212-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (346,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_20131.pdf\" title=\"See the Flyer (PDF)\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-210\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Polyvagal-syndromes2.jpg\" alt=\"Polyvagal-syndromes2\" style=\"border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;\" width=\"750\" height=\"300\" width=\"750\" height=\"300\" /></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>The Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute is proud to present another in a series of post advanced courses, taught by Dr. Peter A Levine. These classes are designed to enhance and extend your skillsets that you have been developing in the 3 year SE® Training.&nbsp;<br /><br />Location: <a href=\"http://book.bestwestern.com/bestwestern/US/CA/Corte-Madera-hotels/BEST-WESTERN-PLUS-Corte-Madera-Inn/Hotel-Overview.do?propertyCode=05259\" title=\"Corte Madera Inn\'s homepage.\" target=\"_blank\">Corte Madera Best Western Inn</a> -&nbsp;56 Madera Blvd &nbsp;Corte Madera, CA 94925</p> <p>Dates: April 18th-22nd, 2013</p> <p>Price: $1495 ($200 if you sign up before March 18th!)</p> <p>How to Enroll: Call 303-652-4035 or email <a href=\"mailto:info@traumahealing.com\">info@traumahealing.com</a>&nbsp;(subject: Master Class Enrollement)</p> <p>Click \"Read More\" to the right to see the class description</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>  <!--more-->  <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div style=\"background-color: #c9c9c9; color: #2c1dgf; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, San-serif;\"> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">A Master Class With SE Founder</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Peter A Levine, PhD</p> <p>The Polyvagal Theory of Stephen Porges, PhD, is a critically important neuro-scientific map for informing precise Somatic Experiencing® interventions. This is particularly true when working directly with SE® bodywork. Porges’ theory guides us in precisely assessing where a client is stuck so that we can support their movement out of shutdown and numbness, to contained arousal, and then to establish core equilibrium, social engagement and enduring feelings of presence, vitality and goodness. Preparing you, the therapist, to competently achieve these lofty (though attainable) goals is the aim of this Master Class.</p> <p>In addition, we will delve into how SE® based bodywork can treat complex syndromes caused by core autonomic dysregulation. These syndromes include migraines, asthma, fibromyalgia, Irritable Bowel Syndrome, Chronic Fatigue Syndrome, Regional Complex Pain Syndrome, as well as, low heart rate or blood pressure, certain cardiac arrhythmias, light headedness, fainting (syncope), and a variety of auto-immune diseases. You will learn why individuals frequently present with these problematic and mutating symptoms, and how they are also associated with various anxiety disorders and depressive conditions. We will expand upon our basic SE® techniques and discover how to treat these syndromes as a cohesive whole. The class will be a mixture of didactic lecture, live demonstrations and hands-on experiential practice.</p> <p>While this training is primarily for individuals who have completed their advanced level training by the time of the master class, it will also be opened to a few skilled body workers who have completed their intermediate level training. While the focus of this special class is on advanced applications of SE Bodywork, it is also open to psycho therapists with some bodywork experience who are wishing to advance their skills.</p> <p><em>Suggested Preparation</em></p> <p>It is important to have (re) read chapters 5&amp;6 in: <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/In-Unspoken-Voice-Releases-Restores/dp/1556439431/ref=pd_bxgy_b_img_y\" title=\"Amazon Page for In an Unsoken Voice\" target=\"_blank\">In an Unspoken Voice; How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness</a>. Additionally, it would be useful to review some of Dr. Porges book: <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Polyvagal-Theory-Neurophysiological-Communication-Self-regulation/dp/0393707008\" title=\"Amazon page for Polyvagal Theory\" target=\"_blank\">The Polyvagal Theory: Neurophysiological Foundations of Emotions, Attachment, Communication, and Self-regulation</a> (Norton Series on Interpersonal Neurobiology)</p> </div>','UPDATED---Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes - Master Class in Corte Madera, Ca','','inherit','open','open','','211-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',211,'http://localhost:8888/speed/211-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (347,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/attachment_hero.jpg\" alt=\"UCLA Conference - Attachment and Neuroplasticity\" style=\"border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;\" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>We are happy to announce that March 8th through the 10th, Dr. Levine has been invited to speak at UCLA\'s Extension and Lifespan Learning Institute\'s conference; entitled - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy.</p> <p>This presentation is open to the public. For more information, <a href=\"https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/default.aspx\" title=\"UCLA Extension website\" target=\"_blank\">please visit here:</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/2013%20Attachment%20Conference%20Brochure.pdf\" title=\"Conference Brochure\" target=\"_blank\">PDF brochure is here:</a>&nbsp;</p> <p><a href=\"http://maps.ucla.edu/campus/?locid=83759\" title=\"UCLA interactive map\" target=\"_blank\">Located in the Ackerman Grand Ballroom</a>. (Link will take you to a lovely interactive map of UCLA\'s campus). You\'re welcome.</p>','UCLA Presents - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy','','inherit','open','open','','208-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',208,'http://localhost:8888/speed/208-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (348,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<p align=\"center\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: left;\">Dr. Levine will be in London, England from May 25th to the 26th for the Breath of Life Conference for 2013. This Conference is for Cranial Sacral Therapists, and we are proud to be in partnership with them.</p> <p align=\"center\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: left;\">Dr. Levine will be presenting a keynote, entitled:&nbsp;<a href=\"#keynote\"><b style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Spirituality and Trauma: From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</b></a> as well as a 2 day Post Conference Workshop, entitled: <a href=\"#workshop\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and Change</span></strong></a><a href=\"#workshop\"><strong>Working with Difficult Feelings</strong></a>(Click each link for a short description).&nbsp;</p> <p>The Breath of Life enrollment is available directly through their website. For More information and to enroll, please visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/\" title=\"Breath of Life London\'s website.\" target=\"_blank\">Breath of Life conference website</a></p> <p>Click Read More:</p> <p> <!--more--> </p> <h6 align=\"center\" style=\"line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;\"><a name=\"keynote\">Spirituality and Trauma;&nbsp;From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</a></h6> <p>In the treatment of the effects of trauma, its inherent relationship with spirituality provides a vital link in the therapeutic process.&nbsp; The understanding of a person\'s, felt, spiritual connection is central to the therapeutic process.&nbsp; If we are unable to access a person\'s spirituality, we may find ourselves trapped, as therapists, in areas that are fraught with pitfalls and \"tight corners\".&nbsp; The intimate association between trauma and spirituality suggests therapeutic avenues that support the authentic transformation of traumatic experiences.</p> <p style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><a href=\".../images/stories/articles/bol-2013_UK/bol_large.jpg\" title=\"Link to larger image\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-205\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_small.jpg\" width=\"196\" height=\"277\" alt=\"breath of life small\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 2px solid #246da5;\" width=\"196\" height=\"277\" /></a></p> <p style=\"line-height: 150%;\">&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Through the use of didactic material- including brain research, experiential practice incorporating the bodily \"felt-sense\", and video material, we will introduce Somatic Experiencing® as a way to re-connect with the deep self. &nbsp; The focus will be on developing practical tools to gracefully enhance the relationship between trauma and spirituality within the therapeutic experience. &nbsp;</p> <p style=\"line-height: 150%;\">You can see the event listing from our <a href=\"https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=10\" title=\"Our event listing\" target=\"_blank\">website</a>, or head directly to <a href=\"http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/\" title=\"Breath of Life Homepage\" target=\"_blank\">BOL\'s website</a>.&nbsp;</p> <p><br /> <br /><a name=\"workshop\"></a></p> <h6 align=\"center\" style=\"line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;\"><a name=\"workshop\">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and ChangeWorking with Difficult Feelings</a></h6> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>In doing therapeutic work, therapists are often confused about the role of emotions. Sometimes therapists and body-workers have the idea that they are supposed to avoid emotions, and others may have been trained to “go after them—to get them out.”</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>While it is true that intense emotional eruptions can interfere with one’s life, there is a deeper truth: that helping clients access their natural emotions, and learn from them, is an important part of good depth therapy and an enhancement to life.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Emotional self-regulation, as we shall explore together, is essential to lasting integration and wholeness. In this regard we will explore how certain emotions (such as disgust and anger) are “gatekeepers” and are essential to opening to other feelings which, together, promotes a fuller, wiser, vital and creative life.</p> <p>See the <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_conf_flyer1.pdf\" title=\"Breath of Life Flyer\" target=\"_blank\">Flyer here</a>. Or go to our <a href=\"https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=11\" title=\"SE.com\'s event listing\" target=\"_blank\">Event listing for location info</a>, or head directly to <a href=\"http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/?page_id=491\" title=\"Breath of Life workshop page\" target=\"_blank\">BOL\'s website</a> to enroll</p>','Breath of Life Conference - This May in London, UK','','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',207,'http://localhost:8888/speed/207-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (349,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<h4>Introduction:</h4> <p>Hi everyone, thanks for enrolling in Peter Levine\'s events. We hope you find this an enriching experience, both professionally and personally. This just lays down some ground rules that we have developed over time to establish certain boundaries.&nbsp;</p> <h4>Cancellation Policy: &nbsp;</h4> <p>We\'ve (as in Peter Levine and his representatives - Justin Snavely, and his coordinators) been having issues with people not taking Peter\'s consults seriously, taking a spot and then canceling at the last minute and expecting a refund. This takes away opportunities for other therapists to learn from Peter. So we have had to say that we will gladly refund you your money if you cancel up to 3 days before the event, as that leaves the coordinator enough time to contact the waiting list and get someone to take your spot. But if you can\'t organize yourself enough to do that, and cancel later than the 3 day cut-off, then we reserve the right to keep your money. If you asked to pay by check or cash, we also reserve the right for you to pay us, like a client would a missed appointment. &nbsp;If you are a jerk, then we WILL add you to a list of people that we will ban from any future Peter Levine event. That sucks, and we don\'t want to do it. But it is a possibility. We know that you are all professionals and this is totally the minority and not the norm. &nbsp;We also know that bad stuff happens and there is nothing to do about it, and we promise to honor those occasional, authentic emergencies where you can\'t make it, due to illness, family problems, death, injuries and accidents, all that stuff, and we won\'t be jerks in return and hold onto your money if you have a valid reason. By confirming your order, you promise that you will honor this.&nbsp;</p> <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3em;\">Confidentiality:</span></p> <p>What happens at the Case Consultation, STAYS AT THE CASE CONSULTATION! Ya Dig? This is people\'s private stuff. We are professionals, dangit!</p> <h4>Putting up with tech equipment and your Video Release:</h4> <p>Peter Levine tapes everything. So there is the chance that your voice and image will be recorded, and can be used for training or marketing materials in a variety of formats, media, or venues. You say you are okay with this. You claim no ownership to the material, and will not hold Peter Levine or his representatives responsible for anything that might effect you in some negative way that could possibly happen in the future. In other words, you won\'t sue us.&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Again, by confirming your order, you agree to these things. Thanks for reading, hope it is clear, if you have any issues or questions, or I missed something, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href=\"mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com?subject=Terms%20and%20Conditions\" target=\"_blank\">traumahealing@gmail.com</a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>','Terms and Conditions','','inherit','open','open','','201-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',201,'http://localhost:8888/speed/201-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (350,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<h2>Instructions:</h2> <p>A Demo session between Peter A Levine PhD and Jana, a woman who was profiled on KTLA for her incredible 5 year battle (c. 2010) with PTSD following a full awakening while under Anesthesia.</p> <p>For your convenience and highest quality, Please use the link to download the video directly to your computer. Right-Click on the two links below and choose \"Save Target As...\" or \"Save Link As...\" (depending on your system). Then tell the computer where and what-name you want it saved as. I would recommend saving to the desktop. Then wait a while for it to download. Once it\'s done, find where you saved your file and then play it. It should be compatible with most media players out there.</p> <p>If this doesn\'t work for you, then please use the streaming version below. It can be played inside the browser. Please be patient while it downloads.&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"direct\"></a>Direct Download (Right click and \"Save Link As...\")</h2> <ul> <li> <h3><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"images/stories/video/jana/jana.mp4\">Jana</a>&nbsp;(1.4GB)</h3> </li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"flash\"></a>\"Streaming\" versions&nbsp;</h2> <p>*please be patient as it downloads.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Jana-</h3> <p>{flowplayer size=768x432 img=http://somaticexperiencing.com/Video/preview/jana_img.png}images/stories/video/jana/jana.mp4{/flowplayer}</p> <p>History: Jana was a friend of the coordinator of the class that Peter was holding to teach practioners of Somatic Experiencing® how to engage with Near Death and Anesthesia States. Jana graciously provided herself as a demonstration. Contains segments from KTLA. With permission. This demonstrates what Peter Levine has been discussing for years as one of the MOST OVERLOOKED sources of trauma (as well as the leading factor that leads to future vulnerability to trauma), \"routine\" surgical procedures. It doesn\'t just have to be full awakening, but also a partial or \"threshold\" awakening where there is no memory, but the body remembering being cut into. This is why Dr. Levine is an ardent champion of the immediate adoption of anesthesiologists utilizing EKG scanners, as well as providing local anesthetic, as well as a general pain reliever on par with morphine.:</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>','Somatic Experiencing©: Jana - Full Awakening Under Anesthesia','','inherit','open','open','','202-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',202,'http://localhost:8888/speed/202-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (351,1,'2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','<h2 align=\"center\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">SE Master Class Series:<br />Emotions and Memory – A Hidden Dimension of Somatic Experiencing®</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">September 30th to October 4th, 2012&nbsp;</h2> <h2 align=\"center\">Chester, CT</h2> <p>&nbsp;</p> <address style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">(Open to SE Students who have completed Intermediate and above. Contact the <a title=\"Email Info@traumahealing.com\" href=\"mailto:info@traumahealing.com?subject=SE Master Class - Emotions and Memory with Peter Levine\">Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute</a> to enroll. See the Flyer <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/se_masterclass-emotions_memory_Oct_20121.pdf\" title=\"Event Flyer (PDF)\" target=\"_parent\">Here</a>)</span></address> <p>The Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a four day, exclusive graduate-level training with Peter A. Levine, PhD, recognized author and developer of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model. This workshop is a rare opportunity to study with the originator of SE® focusing on two of the most misunderstood, nuanced, aspects of working with trauma within the SE® Model.</p> <p>In working with trauma, SE® Practitioners are often confused about the roles of emotions and memory in the resolution of trauma; mainly, that SE® doesn’t need to deal with them. This is wholly untrue.</p> <p>While emotions can interfere with trauma therapy, the deeper truth is that helping clients access and learn from their natural emotions is fundamental to good therapy and is an essential part of the healing process. Specifically, we will explore how certain emotions, such as disgust and anger are “gatekeepers,” keys to opening up to other emotions and to living a fuller, wiser, more vital life.</p> <p>Traumatic memory is one of the most misunderstood and contentious issues in trauma treatment today. Part of this confusion stems from a limited comprehension surrounding the nature and complexity of memory. There are multiple memory systems in the brain and body ranging from those most conscious (so called “normal” or declarative memories) to implicit (emotional) and procedural (so called body) memories, which are deeply unconscious. Each of these memory systems must be approached in a uniquemanner and then integrated into a coherent narrative.</p> <p>During this training, we will explore how to work with your clients’ emotions and memories more masterfully within the SE® model, weaving these crucial aspects of experience together through the trauma re-negotiation process. We will also learn skills to avoid the generation of “false memories”, and to ensure the maximum resolution and integration of traumatic experience and the restoration of wholeness.</p>','Emotions and Memory – A Hidden Dimension of Somatic Experiencing®','','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:29:24','2014-05-22 02:29:24','',199,'http://localhost:8888/speed/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
