INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (364,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" title=\"Full Size\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" alt=\"Case_consult\" width=\"612\" height=\"612\" /></a></p> <p>The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and demonstrations with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>\"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner.\" </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p> </p> <p>Please contact Joan Luly for <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/caseconsultflyer1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">more information</a>: joansehealing@mac.com. Also, view our PDF\'s for <a href=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/registration_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">sign up forms</a> and information about submitting as a demo client.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>','See Peter Work in San Diego, November 5th','','inherit','open','open','','193-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',193,'http://localhost:8888/speed/193-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (365,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf\" title=\"Consult Flyer\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-203\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf\" width=\"150\" height=\"194\" alt=\"LA consult flyer v3-mar-2013 web\" style=\"padding: 4px; border: 2px solid #246da5;\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and supervision with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>\"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner.\" </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p>&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?option=com_eventbooking&amp;view=category&amp;Itemid=110\" title=\"Event Page\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Only the waiting list is available. Click here.</strong></span></a></p> <ul> <li><a href=\"https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=1\">All Day Registration</a>: (11am-6pm, worth 2 Consult Hours)<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong></strong></span></li> <li><a href=\"https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=3\">Afternoon (2nd half) Registration</a>: (3pm-6pm, worth 1 Consult Hour)</li> <li><a href=\"https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=2\">Morning (1st Half) Registration</a>:&nbsp;(11am-2pm, worth 1 Consult Hour)</li> </ul> <p>Please contact Victoria Mihich for <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">more information</a>: <a href=\"mailto:%20Victoria4PeterLevine@yahoo.com\">Victoria4PeterLevine@yahoo.com</a>.</p> <p>If you are interested in having Peter see a client of yours, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href=\"mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com\">traumahealing@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;with the following information:</p> <ol> <li>First name and age of client.</li> <li>Brief list of relevant trauma history (Including the age that it occurred)</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is stuck.</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is advancing.</li> <li>Why do you specifically want Peter to see this client.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <p>NOTE: NO cancellations can be made after March 20th, 2013. Thank you.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>','UPDATED***Peter Levine Group Case Consultation in Los Angeles - March 23rd! - Sold Out','','inherit','open','open','','204-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',204,'http://localhost:8888/speed/204-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (366,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" title=\"Full Size\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" alt=\"Case_consult\" width=\"612\" height=\"612\" /></a></p> <p>The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and supervision with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>\"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner.\" </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://events.constantcontact.com/register/event?llr=qbahuwcab&amp;oeidk=a07e6rljj4m88755a32\" title=\"Constant Contact Event Page - Enroll Now!\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>You can register here. Space is extremely limited.</strong></span></a></p> <p>Please contact Joan Luly for <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/caseconsultflyer1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">more information</a>: <a href=\"mailto:joansehealing@mac.com\">joansehealing@mac.com</a>.</p> <p>If you are interested in having Peter see a client of yours, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href=\"mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com\">traumahealing@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;with the following information:</p> <ol> <li>First name and age of client.</li> <li>Brief list of relevant trauma history (Including the age that it occurred)</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is stuck.</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is advancing.</li> <li>Why do you specifically want Peter to see this client.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <p>NOTE: NO cancellations can be made after January 16th, 2013. Thank you.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>','Peter Levine Group Case Consultation in San Diego - January 19th!','','inherit','open','open','','200-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',200,'http://localhost:8888/speed/200-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (367,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Priscilla Warner\'s blog\" href=\"http://priscillawarnerbooks.com\">Priscilla Warner</a>, Author of <em><a title=\"Her books Amazon page - because we appreciate the free promotion.\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Learning-Breathe-Yearlong-Quest-Bring/dp/1439181071/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1318165624&amp;sr=1-1\">Learning to Breathe</a>&nbsp;</em>was interviewed by Ann Curry on NBC\'s <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"The Today Show Video timeline - Ms. Warner is at 8:40am Sept 23rd,2011\" href=\"http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/35133959/ns/today/t/watch-latest-today-video/\">Today Show</a>, and talked about her book and her year-long journey to overcome anxiety. The subject of trauma came up, and she shared that she used EMDR and \"another wonderful, exciting therapy called Somatic Experiencing.\"&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p> </p> <p>So, we are excited by this very public mention, and present it to you here.&nbsp;</p> <p>Check it out.&nbsp;</p> <p> <object codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=10,0,32,18\" classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" height=\"245\" width=\"420\"> <param name=\"FlashVars\" value=\"launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245\" /> <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"always\" /> <param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" /> <param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" /> <param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640\" /><embed height=\"245\" width=\"420\" src=\"http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640\" wmode=\"transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" flashvars=\"launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"></embed> </object> </p> <p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #999; margin-top: 5px; background: transparent; text-align: center; width: 420px;\">Visit msnbc.com for <a style=\"text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;\" href=\"http://www.msnbc.msn.com\">breaking news</a>, <a href=\"http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032507\" style=\"text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;\">world news</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032072\" style=\"text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;\">news about the economy</a></p>','Priscilla Warner mentions trauma therapy on Today show','','inherit','open','open','','189-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',189,'http://localhost:8888/speed/189-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (368,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p><img class=\" size-full wp-image-185\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Peterheadshot_twitter.jpg\" width=\"360\" height=\"270\" alt=\"Peterheadshot_twitter\" style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial;\" width=\"360\" height=\"270\" /> <img class=\" size-full wp-image-186\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/vanderkolkportret1.jpg\" width=\"196\" height=\"270\" alt=\"Bessel van der Kolk Pic\" style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial;\" width=\"1456\" height=\"2008\" /></p> <p><img class=\" size-full wp-image-187\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Meadows_plain_2011lg.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"125\" alt=\"Meadows logo\" width=\"864\" height=\"216\" /></p> <p>Thanks to The <a style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; font-size: 16px;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"The Meadows Homepage\" href=\"http://www.themeadows.org/\">Meadows Addiction Treatment Center</a>,&nbsp;Dr. Levine will be doing two events on the Eastern Seaboard this September, based on his best-selling book - In an Unspoken Voice, How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness. He will be joined in Boston by trauma pioneer, Bessel van der Kolk, M.D.</p> <p>These presentations, designed for therapists, but approachable by all, will be a whirlwind tour, starting at the very beginnings of the animal world, through human development and our developing nervous system, onto the ethological connections to trauma. Several case studies and video examples will be shown in this dynamic and exciting events - one of my favorites.&nbsp;</p> <p>Bessel van der Kolk is a premiere researcher on trauma, author of the seminal book <em><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Link to Dr. van der Kolk\'s work\" href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=23:traumatic-stress-the-effects-of-overwhelming-experience-on-mind-body-and-society-by-bessel-a-van-der-kolk&amp;catid=11&amp;Itemid=4\">Traumatic Stress</a></em></p> <p><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Find info and register for New York\" href=\"http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992641\">New York City</a>&nbsp;</p> <p>AMA theater on 7th Avenue, will be on September 16.</p> <p><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Find info and register for Boston, Mass\" href=\"http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653\">Boston</a></p> <p><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Find info and register for Boston, Mass\" href=\"http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653\"></a>featuring Bessel van der Kolk, author of the seminal book, Traumatic Stress, &nbsp;September 23rd.</p> <p> </p>','Dr. Levine presents in Boston and NY this September!','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',188,'http://localhost:8888/speed/188-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (369,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<h2>Instructions:</h2> <p>On this page are two videos that are guided demonstrations of SE®, \"Ray - Iraqi War Vet\" and \"Baby Jack.\" There are two copies of each. A <a href=\"#direct\">direct download version</a> and a <a href=\"#flash\">flash player version</a>:</p> <p>For your convenience and highest quality, I have links to download these files directly to your computer. Right-Click on the two links below and choose \"Save Target As...\" or \"Save Link As...\" (depending on your system). Then tell the computer where and what-name you want it saved as. I would recommend saving to the desktop. Then wait a while for it to download. Once it\'s done, find where you saved your file and then play it. It should be compatible with most media players out there.</p> <p>If this doesn\'t work for you, then please use the flash player versions below. they are both in flash video format, and can be played inside the browser.&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"direct\"></a>Direct Download (Right click and \"Save Link As...\")</h2> <ul> <li> <h3><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"images/stories/video/uk_pbr_se_vids/se_militaryrev6.6small.mp4\">Ray - Iraqi War Vet</a>&nbsp;(131MB)</h3> </li> <li> <h3><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/baby_jack-final1.mp4\">Baby Jack</a>&nbsp;(93.4 MB)</h3> </li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <h2><a name=\"flash\"></a>Flash player versions&nbsp;</h2> <h3>Ray - Iraqi War Vet -&nbsp;</h3> <p>{flowplayer size=720x405 img=http://somaticexperiencing.com/Video/preview/se_military.jpg}images/stories/video/uk_pbr_se_vids/se_militaryrev6.6small.mp4{/flowplayer}</p> <p>*please be patient as it downloads.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Baby Jack -</h3> <p>{flowplayer size=720x480 img=http://somaticexperiencing.com/Video/preview/baby_jack.jpg}images/stories/video/uk_pbr_se_vids/baby_jack-final.mp4{/flowplayer}</p>','Somatic Experiencing©: A therapeutic approach to the needs of Iraq and Afghani Soldiers & Baby Jack','','inherit','open','open','','184-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',184,'http://localhost:8888/speed/184-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (370,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','</p><img class=\" size-full wp-image-181\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/ale_duarte1.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"380\" /> <p>Our good friend Ale Duarte, who\'s truly inspirational work leading trauma disaster teams after the Thailand Tsunami, Hurricane Katrina, Sichuan Province, and now in Japan, was recognized and profiled by Japanese News Service NHK <span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><sub><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/english/movie/feature201105250915.html\">(Permalink)</a>.&nbsp;</sub></span></p> <p>Ale is a gifted SE practitioner, and one of the most amazing people ever. Please watch.&nbsp;</p>  <p>{bo_videojs width=[640] height=[380] autoplay=[false] loop=[false] video_mp4=[images/stories/video/ale_nhk/ale_duarte.mp4]  image=[\"images/stories/video/ale_nhk/ale_duarte.jpeg\"]}   Courtesy of NHK.','Ale Duarte on NHK!','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',182,'http://localhost:8888/speed/182-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (371,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p>Dr. Levine will be offering a Group Case Consultation in San Diego Ca on February 5th, 2011, from 11am - 6:30pm. This day is offered to therapists only, and all levels of SE trainees and practitioners.&nbsp;</p> <p>For more information, <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sd_consult_flyer.pdf\" title=\"SD case consult\" target=\"_blank\">please see attached PDF</a>, or check the events calendar page.&nbsp;</p>','Case Consult in San Diego, California - November 5th, 2011','','inherit','open','open','','180-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',180,'http://localhost:8888/speed/180-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (372,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<object width=\"400\" height=\"227\"><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=17820758&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=00ADEF&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" /><embed src=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=17820758&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=00ADEF&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" width=\"400\" height=\"227\"></embed></object><p><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/17820758\">Peter Levine receives the Lifetime Achievement Award from USABP</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/user1349394\">Peter Levine</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>','USABP Lifetime Achievement Award','','inherit','open','open','','178-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',178,'http://localhost:8888/speed/178-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (373,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p>Dr. Levine has been awarded the lifetime achievement award from the <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"USABP Homepage\" href=\"http://usabp.org/displaycommon.cfm?an=3\">United States Association for Body Psychotherapy</a> (USABP), at their annual conference October 22nd through the 24th at John F. Kennedy University in Pleasant Hills, Ca. &nbsp;</p> <p>Peter is thrilled to receive such an honor, and&nbsp;will be giving the Keynote address on October 23rd, as well as teaching a post-conference workshop and will be serving on the Conference panel in the afternoon.</p> <p><img class=\" size-full wp-image-176\" style=\"background-color: #eeeeee; display: block; padding: 4px;\" alt=\"USABP-conference\" height=\"85\" width=\"300\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/USABP-conference1.jpg\" width=\"564\" height=\"160\" /></p> <p>For more information, or to <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Enroll NOW!\" href=\"http://www.usabp.org/displayconvregister.cfm?convnbr=7093\">enroll</a>, please check out the USABP Conference <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"USABP Conference Page\" href=\"http://usabp.org/displayconvention.cfm?conventionnbr=7093\">Homepage</a>.&nbsp;</p>','Dr. Levine Receives a Lifetime Achievement Award From USABP!','','inherit','open','open','','177-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',177,'http://localhost:8888/speed/177-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (374,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p><em>For members of the Somatic Experiencing®Training Program Only:</em></p> <p>Peter is coming to the San Francisco area to recieve a Lifetime Achievment award from the <a href=\"http://usabp.org/displayconvention.cfm?conventionnbr=7093\" title=\"USABP Conference Info\" target=\"_blank\">United States Association for Body Pschotherapy</a>.</p> <p> </p> <p style=\"float: right; background-color: #eeeeee; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #dddddd;\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-171\" alt=\"Peter Pic\" height=\"150\" width=\"200\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/esalen21.jpg\" width=\"2592\" height=\"1944\" /></p> <p>As part of his lifetime achievement award with <a href=\"http://usabp.org/\" title=\"USABP Homepage\" target=\"_blank\">USABP</a>, Dr. Levine will be offering two events in the Tiburon/Northern California area. The first will be a one-day Group Case Consultation that is open to ALL levels of SE<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">®&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">training on October 28th, 2010. The second will be a 3 day workshop for SE Practitioners and Students who have completed Advanced Level I on dealing with Near Death and Anesthesia states, October 29th, through 31st, 2010. </span></span></p> <p> </p> <p>This is the first part of a two part class, that Dr. Levine has taught throughout Europe, and is finally bringing to the US.&nbsp;</p>  <!--more-->  <h5 style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Group Case Consultation - October 28th, 2010. Open to all levels.</h5> <p>Location:Tiburon, TBA</p> <p>Costs/enrollment:&nbsp;Please contact coordinator&nbsp;<a style=\"outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; font-size: 18px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;\" href=\"mailto:andrea@easethebody.com\" title=\"Email Andrea Smith\" target=\"_blank\">Andrea Smith</a> for more information.</p> <p> </p> <h5 style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Through the Eye of the Needle: Working with Near Death and Anesthesia States: For Post-Advanced Somatic Experiencing® Practitioners Only:</h5> <p><img class=\" alignright size-full wp-image-172\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vortex-8001.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" alt=\"Vortex\" style=\"float: right;\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" /></p> <p>In the USA over 29 million patients utilize powerful dissociative and amnesic agents…“general anesthesia”. Some individuals experience states of death from which they are revived. In fact,some of the deepest and seemingly most intractable trauma symptoms occur with clients who become “stuck” in these altered states of consciousness. Yet these same near death experiences(NDE’s) hold the extraordinary potential for deep positive and enduring personal spiritual transformation. All traumas involve an encounter with threat, and hence, a touch with death. This workshop, broken up over two classes, is the next step to enlarge your range of competency in order to guide your client through this perilous landscape. Participants will be taught the theoretical framework for understanding altered states and near death encounters and how to:</p> <ul> <li>access and liberate problematic fixations</li> <li>develop and refine perceptual skills and practical tools</li> <li>resolve difficult somatic symptoms</li> <li>facilitate authentic spiritual experiences</li> <li>address these delicate states utilizing table touch work (experiential).</li> </ul> <p><img class=\" alignright size-full wp-image-173\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/WaterVortex1.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" alt=\"Water Vortex\" style=\"float: right;\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" /></p> <p> </p> <blockquote>God of the traumatized, grant Your empathetic, all understanding comfort of Your beloved and innocentchildren all over the world who have suffered the unspeakable terror of anesthesia awareness. Hold with gentle firmness those who cannot express what happened to them or how traumatic their experience was and is. ~ <em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Prayer for Anesthesia Awareness Network</span></em></blockquote> <p>This is the first of two parts for working with Near Death States. Eye of the Needle Part II is planned for April 1st through the 4th. Don\'t missed this exciting opportunity.&nbsp;</p> <p>Click <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Sign up form\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/eontiburonsignup1.pdf\">here</a> the Sign up form. For more information on the class, please contact coordinator&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:andrea@easethebody.com\" title=\"Email Andrea SMith\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; font-size: 18px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;\">Andrea Smith</a>.</p>','Two Workshops for SEP\'s being held in Northern California','','inherit','open','open','','175-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',175,'http://localhost:8888/speed/175-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `sep_posts` VALUES (375,1,'2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><img class=\" size-full wp-image-166\" alt=\"Thesis-title\" height=\"158\" width=\"300\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/Thesis-title.jpg\" style=\"background-color: #eeeeee; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #dddddd;\" width=\"1173\" height=\"616\" /></p> <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Peter Levine\'s 1976 Doctoral dissertation,&nbsp;<em><a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Peter Levine\'s thesis\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/Peter_A_Levine-Thesis1.pdf\">Accumulated Stress, Reserve Capacity, and Disease</a></em>, is now available online as a <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Download Adobe Acrobat\" href=\"http://www.adobe.com/products/reader/\">PDF</a>. For those of you interested in reading one of Peter\'s earliest documents regarding the connection between ANS discharge and the releasing of system stress, please enjoy. I have attached the abstract as well. We are looking to convert it to word and .html as well.&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p> <p> </p> <p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\"> </p>  <!--more-->  <p> </p> <p> </p> <p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Abstract</p> <p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">The underlying theme of this paper is that the accumulation of stress affects the reserve capacity of an organism, both in the maintenance of its functional integrity and inthe resolution of subsequent exposures to stress. Stress isdefined in terms of a reaction resulting from stimuli whichsufficiently activate the autonomic nervous system (ANS) andis either resolved or accumulated depending on whether the pre-stimulus baseline is re-established or not.</p> <p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Accumulated stress profoundly influences the totality of organismic functioning, and is expressed essentially through three bi-polar effector systems: In the realm of the autonomic, the effector system is the sympathetic and parasympathetic visceral outflow. For the somatic, it is paired movers, like extensor/flexors; and metabolically stress is expressed (though less distinctly) by, for example, catabolic/anabolic and inflammatory/anti-inflammatory endocrine reactions.</p> <p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">The response to stress is defined as occurring sequentiallyin two phases, charge and discharge: When the charging(sympathetic) phase is followed by a<img class=\" size-full wp-image-168\" title=\"Parasympathetic/Sympathetic Nervous System Cycle\" alt=\"parasympathetic/sympathetic Autonomic Nervous System cycle\" height=\"81\" width=\"257\" src=\"http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/parasympathetic-sympathetic-cyclejpg.jpg\" style=\"background-color: #eeeeee; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #dddddd;\" width=\"767\" height=\"242\" /> parasympathetic discharge of equal magnitude, then pre-activation homeostasis is reestablished and the stress is said to be resolved. On the other hand, it is shown that under certain physiologic conditions (and behaviorally where mobilization--i,e.,somatic response to stress--is blocked), the charge phase is no longer balanced by rebound. In these cases activation is not resolved and the stress becomes incorporated within the organism, as a diminished adaptational capacity.</p> <p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">The basic physiologic relations of the autonomic, sympatheticand parasympathetic, can be represented by a simple mechanical analogy (the \"Zeeman Machine\") which exhibits properties described by a relatively new branch of mathematical topology, Catastrophe theory. The visualization gained by this re-presentation offers new insights into the nature and mechanisms by which stress accumulates. It also suggests paradigms by which stress, once it has already become internalized, may be successively resolved towards re-establishinga fuller adaptational range/reserve capacity.</p> <p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">In this regard, various holistic systems of healing areseen to focus their efforts towards detecting and treatingthese accumulation imbalances and reduced capacities evenbefore they become symptomatic and pathologic. It is the view of this work that a wide range of \"stress diseases\" with varied symptoms and obscure aetiologies are the final-- pathologic — expression of this loss in resiliency. That the accumulation of stress is the underlying stratum in certain disease syndromes is tested by measuring autonomic levels underlying certain blood pressure responses of a hospitalized population. It is not possible, however,to measure the sympathetic and parasympathetic components directly (since they are expressed as a single output vector, blood pressure). For this reason a systems analysis of the cardio-vascular system, based on well known experimental parameters, but with variable set point and gain levels, is constructed. A set of blood pressure response curves is generated and compared with the hospitalized population. The fit of these with the experimental data is surprisingly good. In addition, the prognosis for five groups in the hospitalized population is predicted accurately by the model, where as no such predictions could be made on the basis of the raw data.The accumulation of stress, defined in terms of the autonomic nervous system, influences many, if not all, other systems. The concept of an autonomic hypothalamic \"hub\"around which behavior is organized and executed is illustrated to clarify some of these extended relationships. Specifically,the hypothalamic links between autonomic-endocrine, as well as somatic mobilizing systems, are examined in this context. In addition, examples illustrating the potential for the wide and varied symptomatologies of their \"mis-integration\" (autonomic-endocrine-somatic) in the stress diseases are presented. Some possibilities for pre-symptomatic diagnosis, whereby stress accumulation is detected before the development of debilitating symptoms and tissue pathologies, are investigated as well. These stress diseases are shown, in a selected set of examples, to have underlying patterns of unresolved stress that can be understood in terms of their topologic configurations in catastrophe space.</p> <p>Read the rest of Dr. Levine\'s thesis <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Peter Levine\'s thesis\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/Peter_A_Levine-Thesis1.pdf\">here</a>.</p> <p>Does require Adobe Acrobat v. 9.0 and above. Don\'t have <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Download Adobe Acrobat\" href=\"http://www.adobe.com/products/reader/\">adobe acrobat</a>? Follow the link.&nbsp;</p> <p>Or try a faster, lightweight version through <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"Download Foxit Reader\" href=\"http://www.foxitsoftware.com/pdf/reader/addons.php\">Foxit reader</a>.</p>','Peter\'s Doctoral Thesis is online','','inherit','open','open','','169-revision-v1','','','2014-05-22 02:31:09','2014-05-22 02:31:09','',169,'http://localhost:8888/speed/169-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
